6	Grandfather clause - Wikipedia	A grandfather clause (or grandfather policy) is a provision in which an old rule  continues to apply to some existing situations while a new rule will apply to all  future cases. Those exempt from the new rule are said to have grandfather rights  or acquired rights, or to have been grandfathered in. ... Examples included  imposition of poll taxes and residency and literacy tests.	https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grandfather_clause
